At the time, our project used **three different CSS frameworks**â€”a nightmare for any frontend engineer.

Every new design meant figuring out which set of components and styles it referenced.  
It was inefficient, error-prone, and painful to maintainâ€”plus the performance hit from loading redundant styles.

Iâ€™d seen this problem before, and had led similar refactors in a previous job.


